leads.lead_text: Stipules cordate or broadly ovate (often wider than long); corolla 15–25 mm long, usually pale red or orange-red with a basal yellow blotch; widespread
Stipules lanceolate or narrowly ovate; corolla 30–40 mm long, dark red or purplish; mainly East Gippsland
Plants usually prostrate; leaflets less than 3.5 cm long; flowers mostly 1 or 2; peduncles 1–3 cm long
Robust woody climbers; leaflets more than 4 cm long; flowers in cluster of threes forming long, many-flowered racemes up to 20 cm long
